<StringTableFile xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema">
  <Name>conversations\x_labyrinth\x6091_cnpcfathom_crefton_philethis</Name>
  <NextEntryID>1</NextEntryID>
  <EntryCount>58</EntryCount>
  <Entries>
    <Entry>
      <ID>1</ID>
      <DefaultText>As you approach the philethis, you see that its glass mask - or face - is covered in a spiderweb of fractures identical to those you inflicted on the philethis outside the clocktower. A septic mist hisses from the cracks, sinking rather than rising as it dissipates.

The philethis says but a single word: "Maroon." Without further explication, it seems to turn in upon itself, and in an instant, is gone.

{WORDPLAY: "Maroon" here conjures the off-red color, the sense of castaway, and the slang term for "idiot." I doubt this will be replicable in any foreign language, so maybe just go for a reddish color that carries *some* secondary meaning.}</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>2</ID>
      <DefaultText>As far as you can tell, this philethis looks exactly the same as the one you met before - perhaps *is* the same.

As you approach, its hidden body seems to draw a deep breath, but nothing emerges: no words, no noise, no exhalation at all.

Its glass mask seems fixed upon you, but it just as easily could be sleeping within. The thing just stands there, as if indifferent, until suddenly it speaks: "How many motes of light spilled upon the ground before you moved the basin?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>3</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>4</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>5</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>6</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>7</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>8</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>9</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>10</ID>
      <DefaultText>"None."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>11</ID>
      <DefaultText>"One."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>12</ID>
      <DefaultText>"A few."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>13</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Many."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>14</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't know."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>15</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>16</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Yes. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>17</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No. </DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>18</ID>
      <DefaultText>The yol-calf gets sour milk from its mother's teat. Those that seek sweeter suckling waste away but never weep. The yol-herder spills salt tears but the earth thirsts without tasting." Its mask darkens, but its voice carries on with flat indifference. "Did you drink the light?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>19</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis's glass face shimmers with iridescence for several moments before it speaks again.


</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>20</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What do you mean?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>21</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I left it in the basin."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>22</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I drank in the light."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>23</ID>
      <DefaultText>"I don't know."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>24</ID>
      <DefaultText>A staticky hiss spills from whatever means of speech the philethis employs. At last, without accusation or guidance, it says simply, "You know."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>25</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis leans its bulk toward you, ever so slightly. "No. You do not know the light. Ask."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>26</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis leans its bulk toward you, ever so slightly. "No. You will burn in the light. Ask."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>27</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis leans its bulk toward you, ever so slightly. "You do. But ask."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>28</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What did the light mean? What do your questions mean?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>29</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why are you here? *How* are you here?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>30</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>31</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What can you tell me about this place?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>32</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Let me try again - what *will* you tell me about this place?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>33</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>34</ID>
      <DefaultText>Almost with a sigh, it answers, "Everything."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>35</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Nothing."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>36</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What are you, anyway?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>37</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Why do I keep meeting you?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>38</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>39</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Can you help me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>40</ID>
      <DefaultText>"At this point, I'll take whatever help I can get, clammy or otherwise."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>41</ID>
      <DefaultText>"So you won't help me?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>42</ID>
      <DefaultText>"What is the question?"</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>43</ID>
      <DefaultText>"Farewell."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>44</ID>
      <DefaultText>The thing's voice warbles, as if with an echo that precedes the sound itself. Eventually, words come. "When the question is known, the answer is but a conclusion."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>45</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis cocks its spheroid head and answers without emotion. "I have always been here."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>46</ID>
      <DefaultText>"No. We shall not."

A moment later, its robes seem to sweep inward, and it disappears.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>47</ID>
      <DefaultText>"That is not the question."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>48</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>49</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis's face shines pearlescent, and its voice, for once, is heavy relief. "Now you understand."

A moment later, its robes seem to sweep inward, and it disappears.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>50</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>51</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>52</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>53</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>55</ID>
      <DefaultText />
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>56</ID>
      <DefaultText>A long groan sounds from within the philethis's heavy robes. The voice that follows seems high and piping by contrast. "A debauchee, his other diversions exhausted, sought the clammy embrace of a nychthemeron. The romance ended tastefully, as did the libertine."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>57</ID>
      <DefaultText>The robes rise and fall, suggesting the movement of smaller things beneath. Then, it answers. "In her ivory tower, the Lady hears howling from the observation cells. Notes are taken. Actions are not."</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>58</ID>
      <DefaultText>The philethis's silence is answer enough.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
    <Entry>
      <ID>59</ID>
      <DefaultText>You can feel no thoughts at all from within the robed figure.</DefaultText>
      <FemaleText />
    </Entry>
  </Entries>
